From 61b27c63ca76cdadd9de3b6a23664894f21966b0 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Filippo Luca Ferretti <filippoluca.ferretti@outlook.com>
Date: Tue, 14 Apr 2026 14:04:45 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 5/5] Add CK MFMA GEMM integration for accelerated tile_matmul
 on AMD GPUs

Implement block-level GEMM using AMD MFMA intrinsics as an alternative
to cuBLASDx for tile_matmul operations on CDNA GPUs.

Key components:
- ck_gemm.h: MFMA-based block GEMM for FP32, FP64, FP16 (promoted to FP32)
  using mfma_f32_16x16x4f32 and mfma_f64_16x16x4f64 instructions
- build_ck_dot(): generates device function source code (no LTO linking
  needed since hipRTC compiles everything in one unit)
- Dispatch integration in builtins.py to select CK or mathdx at codegen time
- Build system flags: --ck flag (requires --hip), WP_ENABLE_CK define

The CK approach differs from mathdx by generating complete __device__
function definitions that are embedded in the kernel source and compiled
by hipRTC, rather than producing LTOIR binaries linked via nvJitLink.

Targets CDNA1+ GPUs (MI100, MI210, MI250X, MI300X) with wavefront-based
tile distribution across the thread block.
